Green tea contains catechins and theanine as major ingredients and has been reported to have various beneficial influences on human health.

 It is reported that the drinking green tea is inversely associated with serum homocysteine level in elderly.

 However the effect of green tea consumption on cognitive dysfunction is not clinically clarified.

 The purpose of this study is to investigate the effects of green tea consumption on homocysteine metabolism and cognitive dysfunction in elderly with impaired cognitive function.

